---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="RSS Feed - Code & Karma Blog">
  <main class="min-h-screen">
    <div class="container py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6 neon-gradient-text">RSS Feed</h1>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground mb-8">
            Stay up to date with the latest posts from Code & Karma blog using RSS.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">üì° What is RSS?</h2>
            <p>
              RSS (Really Simple Syndication) is a web feed format that allows you to stay up-to-date with your favorite websites in a simple way. Instead of manually checking for new content, RSS feeds automatically deliver new posts directly to your RSS reader.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">üîó RSS Feed URL</h2>
            <p class="mb-4">Our RSS feed is available at:</p>
            <div class="bg-muted p-4 rounded-lg font-mono text-sm">
              <code>https://karma-and-code.dev/rss.xml</code>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <a href="/rss.xml" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 transition-colors">
                ‚Üí View RSS Feed
              </a>
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">üì± Popular RSS Readers</h2>
            <p class="mb-4">Here are some popular RSS readers you can use:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Feedly</strong> - Web-based, mobile apps available</li>
              <li><strong>Inoreader</strong> - Feature-rich web reader</li>
              <li><strong>NewsBlur</strong> - Social RSS reader</li>
              <li><strong>NetNewsWire</strong> - Native macOS and iOS app</li>
              <li><strong>Feedbin</strong> - Premium web-based reader</li>
              <li><strong>The Old Reader</strong> - Google Reader-like interface</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">üöÄ How to Subscribe</h2>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-3">
              <li>Choose an RSS reader from the list above</li>
              <li>Create an account if needed</li>
              <li>Look for an "Add Feed" or "Subscribe" button</li>
              <li>Copy and paste our RSS URL: <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-1 rounded">https://karma-and-code.dev/rss.xml</code></li>
              <li>Enjoy automatic updates whenever we publish new content!</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
          
          <div class="mt-12 text-center">
            <a 
              href="/" 
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg bg-primary/10 border border-primary/30 text-primary hover:bg-primary/20 transition-all neon-button-glow"
            >
              ‚Üê Back to Blog
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    color: hsl(var(--foreground));
  }
  
  .prose h2 {
    color: hsl(var(--foreground));
  }
  
  .prose p {
    color: hsl(var(--muted-foreground));
  }
  
  .prose code {
    background: hsl(var(--muted));
    color: hsl(var(--foreground));
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.875em;
  }
  
  .prose ul li,
  .prose ol li {
    color: hsl(var(--muted-foreground));
  }
  
  .prose strong {
    color: hsl(var(--foreground));
  }
</style>